Copa Confraternidad 1988


Memorial Colisseum, Los Angeles, California

[Apr 21]
América [MEX] 2 Peñarol [URU] 2 [5-4pen]
  [Antonio Carlos Santos 66, Luis Roberto Alves 73; Gustavo Matosas 35, 
   Herrera 84]

  [PEN AME: Antonio Carlos Santos, Luis Roberto Alves, Robinson Hernández, 
   Carlos Hermosillo, Guillermo Huerta]
  [PEN PEÑ: Vieira, Gonzalvez, Herrera, Rivero (M), Varán]


NB: Originally this match was to be played as "Copa Interamericana 1987" 
    between CONCACAF Champions Cup 1987 Champion (América) and Copa Libertadores 1987 
    Champion (Peñarol), however, disagreements between CONCACAF, CONMEBOL and the organisers 
    of the match, caused the change of the name of the tournament to "Confraternidad", 
    finally Club América was fined and suspended for 2 years of CONCACAF tournaments. 


